## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the TAIME project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

### Changes Made

**Created:**
- No new files created

**Modified:**
1. `app/layout.tsx` - Added Vercel Analytics component to the root layout
   - Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag as per Next.js App Router best practices
   
2. `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
   - Added `@vercel/analytics` version `^2.0.1` to dependencies
   
3. `package-lock.json` - Updated lock file
   - Installed 223 new packages as dependencies of @vercel/analytics
   - Lock file updated to ensure consistent dependency resolution

### Implementation Details

- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.4 with App Router
- **Package Manager**: npm (detected from package-lock.json)
- **Package Installed**: @vercel/analytics@^2.0.1
- **Integration Point**: Root layout (`app/layout.tsx`)

The Analytics component was added following the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects. The component provides seamless integration with Next.js including automatic route tracking.

### Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with Next.js 16.2.4
✅ TypeScript compilation passed without errors
✅ All 34 routes generated successfully
✅ No linting errors (project uses TypeScript type checking during build)
✅ Package lock file properly updated

### Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the project to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics → Enable)
3. After deployment, verify analytics tracking by checking the browser's Network tab for analytics requests

The implementation preserves all existing code structure and metadata configuration while adding only the minimal necessary changes for Vercel Web Analytics integration.
